	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 31st 4:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, some people may have twinked, some just may have gotten extremely lucky with things dropping, and some may have spent over 2 weeks getting money. If you have just been playing through the levels, you should have at LEAST 300pp with the good weapons you have. Since you are lvl 20, the BIBS is a good sword for you to use, and you DO have another good 1hs. Remember, at your lvl, you will hit for a lot more than 20 or so with the BIBS. That should be good for you till about lvl 25 or so. If you do want to make some money+ leveling at your level, i suggest going to Highpass, and making a gnoll group. There are Ringmail drops here, and rawhide armor. Also, you have a chance at a great shield + a good sword if you hunt a bit here. youll prolly want to keep the sword and the shield if you get them, the shield should last through 35 or so, your *New*, hopefully 1hs sword should last you through about lvl 25, where you can sell that for a bit, and maybe buy something else. Also, if you REALLY want to be frugal, get a guide to Lguk, and shout there for someone to tell you if shin greaves drop. Those are fairly good, no drop legs, and you MIGHT be able to get Shin Guantlets while you are there. If you pick up these, you can sell your old stuff for a few pp or some good pp. If you see someone leave stuff on a corpse of something you cant kill, loot it, there will be most likely some FS weapons or something. At your level, the only real good "easy-cash" method is GLS quest. And that just SUCKS doing it. If you work hard enough though, you might be able to get up near 1kpp in about a week of 3 hours playing periods. Thats all my advice, besides, if you work towards making levels, you will probably be able to get loot along with that. Dont give up, the road is hard but the payoff is good. Last advice-SAVE YOUR MONEY FOR LATER WHEN YOU REALLY NEED IT, BELIEVE ME!<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
