	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wow, i had a lowly mino axe at lvl 9, you got real lucky on that. Anyways, answering your question, DEFINATLY keep the BIBS, just go to Crushbone and collect some CB belts and sell them for 1pp each. when you have maybe 30pp or so, buy a shiny brass shield(best newbie easy to obtain shield in the game), and a mino axe. then just practice both each level until they max out. This way you have more opportunities to buy great deals and actually be able to use the weapons you buy. You will be able to beat the crap out of a lvl 30 giant with a weighted axe for the opening blow, and then rip him apart after that with a faster 1hs+shield combo that you keep in store. Believe me, keep the BIBS, you will use it for a long time, and keep doing small upgrades to your armor and 1hs. It will pay off in the long run, trust me.<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
