<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98065214025281></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98065214025281><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98065214025281>RE: Frustration-Retirement [don't give up!]</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98065214025281#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 28th 3:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Paladins can be soloed, but equipment is your key to success. Right now, I have a paladin that just hit 35 on bristlebane (Diovan).<br><br>I think the biggest factor to me soloing better in lake of ill omen (I went there at lvl21 and had a lot of downtime) was that I was able to get my hands on a mithril 2hander (21 dmg, 28 dly with haste factored in (haste is the effect on the weapon, not from fbss or anything)). I got it at lvl25 and I've been much more effective at soloing since then. My armor is pretty good too (mostly strength boosts, but some dex/wis/etc in there). <br><br>Anyway, most of my items came from chance encounters with a couple of high level folks. If you're not as lucky, still don't give up. Save as much money as you can and first go for a better weapon (the lowest delay, highest damage you can afford). delay always makes a difference, because you want to kill the mob as quick as you can.<br><br>Get an axe of iron back (16dmg, 37dly or something like that -- been using it until lvl25). it's better than your forged blade, and you can get one for around 100pp. that's the quickest solution to your weapon problem if you don't have a lot of cash to spare.<br><br>A good way to make money is to make your way to east/west commons and collect greater lightstones off willowisps. They're rare drops, but you can sell them to people for around 5-6pp each. even better, go to oasis and you can give them to a certain gypsy (forgot the name). Not only do you get exp, but you get an item (a container, so make sure you have an open general slot), which you can sell back to the gypsy for around 7-8pp. Another thing is to collect high quality bear pelts off kodiaks. These are much more rare, but they go for 30-40pp each.<br><br>at 16...I would tell you to hunt in oasis, but that zone is overcrowded a lot of times (at least it was on bristlebane). it's kinda risky too, because everything other than crocodiles/caimans aggro on you.<br><br>a strategy you might try using (if you have root, but I don't know if you get that yet), is to root your opponent if you're running low on hp, back up a bit, and heal yourself. you could even med too until root breaks (so move back a bit and make sure nothing else will jump you). it's hard to tell when root will break (if it even holds), so always be prepared.<br><br>and ac/agi is important more than anything for armor (strength is nice for the extra damage, but it's not that noticeable unless you have over +20 extra strength). agi will help you dodge hits more; I think ac just makes successful hits do less damage (I don't see how it will help you to avoid hits if you're wearing heavy, high ac armor).<br><br>I've said a lot of crap, and I'm not sure how much of it is helpful, but I hope you got something out of it. Take care and have hope.<br><br>Diovan (Bristlebane)<br>Feresta (The Rathe)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
