	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a Dwarven Paladin, I will undoubtedly be slanted towards thinking Dwarven Paladins are the best! My little guy ROCKS and I love playing him. If you want to run the BEST Character/Class combination, then I would say a Dwarf is the way to go! However, you should play what you feel most comfortable and happy with, NOT what the best combination of stats is.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will not be happy with your character otherwise.  If you think an Erudite Paladin or Half-Elf Paladin is best, run one of those.<br><br>In keeping with your question, let me point out that dwarves start with an Agility stat of 70. If your agility stat is below 75, you receive a 50 pt. Armor Class deduction/penalty! So if you do start a Dwarf, make sure you put those all-important 5 points into Agility. I'd split the rest between Strength and Wisdom, skip Intelligence and Charisma all together, and if you really wanted to, throw a point or two into Dex, but that's not really necessary. With any odd points I'd throw them into Strength.  Remember, you will be looked upon as a tank, so Armor Class is king! Put 5 points into Agility if you start a Dwarf.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
