	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nice post Kneesmasher, i also used a ghoulbane at lvls 28-35. It is a good weapon, and since i was an idiot and didnt train in 2hs, i never used any 2hs weapons. Ghoulbane at your level rocks for fighting undead creatures, it procs easy, almost never resisted, has a good dps ratio, and has a great proc. Granted, that 2hs you use is a great weapon,but when you get a Wurmslayer, it will make that look like a rusty weapon. One way to get it is to sell your ghoulbane and 2h practice sword, and hopefully youve been saving up around a k or so, buy the scales used for the Wurmslayer quest. Go do the quest, get your wurmslayer, and revel in the fact of that you ripped someone off SOOOOOOOOOOOOO badly. I used to hit in the high 70's and low 80's consistently when i was lvl 36. Even a Mith2hander cant do that. Trust me, Wurmslayer is worth the price you might pay for it, it does WAYYYYYYY more damage than a Mith 2hander, besides the delay. Plus, you get bash and some more stat adjustment plus ac from a shield. Also, dont try to go get the ghoulbane the "honorable" way, because at lvl 30, you need a full group of 35's to just get that far into the dungeon if you are KoS. And hunting the Shin lord WILL make you KoS in Uguk. this means that whenever you want to go to Lguk for some cash or stuff, you will have to clear everything in your way, hence you destroy your faction with live frogs forever. Not good. Also, i think that you should keep that 2hslash up wit that weapon, when you are not the main tank, i suggest using that instead of Wurm, just for keeping skills up. What else- ah yes, i would definatly take damage over speed weapons. My reasons are if you have a dmg shielded apponent, hence almost every single thing in a non cleared dungeon, you wont get hurt that bad, but youll kill yourself with speed weapons. Also, doing more damage at once is a better taunt then doing a lot of damage over time. Back to GB, if you stick with your levels, cash will flow, and youll be able to buy more stuff. You can also do Ro at your level, its INCREDIBLE exp then, each thing for a mold turned in is a bub of exp. Than you can sell Ro for money hence being able to buy better stuff. As for 2hs, i would keep yours for now, until you can go do Soulfire. Ok, i think i went a lil overboard, but what the hay. Bomb me if ya want hehe.<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
