	   <tr><td colspan=2>Everyone is forgetting my favorite hunting ground and one that brough my from lvl 15 to lv 30 in 10 days.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lake of Ill Omen!  I love that place, still do.  It is essentail to group in there but it can also be soloed (i've done both).  If oyu in a group the best place to camp in your teens is between the River and the Goblin Ruins on the Left side of the Lake ( as your coming From Fiona Vie).  There hunt everything in sight staying clear of the Goblin Ruins (I've seen some poor puller pull every Goblin out of that spot and counted nearly 15 goblins chasing after that poor soul), however I never tried Lull in the ruins and there is invariably one behind the wall that you cannot see (reserve these till at least level 20 or so when they con white to blue- without a very strong group they will kill your entire party due to the fact that no matter how good the puller is 2 always seem to come). Hunting there usssualy consists of Iskar Muaraders, Goblin Agrressors and Battlemasters, Leseer Icebone and Charbone Skeletons (great practice for that Ward undead spell) Sabertooth Tigers and Sarnak Flunkies.  Soloing can be done at around lvl 15 safely in the area to the right of the lake (again as your coming from Fiona Vie) around the general area of the first Abandoned Tower here you can find more of the same types of mosters as listed previously but not quite as hard (make sure you con everything before they aggro on you or you attack them though- everyonce in awhile a yellow or red gets thrown in the mix).  From there move to the Windmill and the to the Sarnak Fortress or Goblin Caves (grouping of course) and then the exp will really flow.  Also a nice thing about the mosters in the area generally carry 1-2pp and change on them.  Most of the time I run around encumbered due to the fact that I have so much coin on my person yet do not want to quite fighting long enough for me to run to the bank in Foina Vie.  A word of Caution about Fiona Vie - once outside the city gates AVIOD EVERYTHING, almost all monsters in the area are lvl 35+, and there's a nasty necro floating around that I've heard is 45+.  Just keep your constantly looking for the black and red spiders and follow the river on up to the Lake of Ill Omen (SoW is helpful in this zone as well as Camo/Invisibilty.  However being a dwarve I luck out sometimes and am able to run directly under the spider avoiding an aggro by shear luck)<br>&nbsp;<br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></tr>
