	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would suggest Crushbone, especially if you are able to play in off-hours. You are a perfect level to help her solo Legos and they should still be pretty good XP for her, not to mention Emissary's and Oracles. You also get the Lego Pads which she can turn in to Canloe Nusback in the Kaladim Warriors Guild (downstairs) and get additional experience for doing that.&nbsp;&nbsp;The pads won't help you much anymore at 19th but should still move her XP bar. If you can get a good group together for the Throne Room and hold it for a while, you can make a ton of experience!  Some of the fastest teen experience in the game that I've ever seen. The spawns are numerous and quick, with Lord Darish spawning frequently and dropping some nice loot. With two Paladins, a healer, maybe a warrior or two and perhaps a rogue or druid, you could literally make several levels in a night holding the TR camp.<br><br>The only drawback to Crushbone is it is crowded during peak times.  There's a reason for that, it's a GREAT zone.  But if you can play during off-hours, most areas will have plenty of Mobs that still give her good XP like the Taskmaster Orc near the Slaver pits.  If you tire of the Throne Room, you can move on up into the Tower and take on Royal Guards (they drop bronze weapons), Crush (for the tunic), The Prophet and even DVinn himself if you have a really good and strong group.  DVinn is tough and not for the faint of heart at sub 20's! Crush was the first Mob to ever hit me for damage in the 40's!  DVinn was the first mob to ever hit me with double attacks over 40 EACH!  If you play in the TR, you will no doubt encounter these guys anyway.  For really fast levelling, it's hard to beat but she will soon outgrow it. I still recall the first time I killed a Lego and got no experience.....it was the passing of an era!<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30 Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
