	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hakadar, my choice, hands down, is Castle Mistmoore.&nbsp;&nbsp;See post above yours concerning Mistmoore Zone, but it offers a challenge, to say the least. Make a mistake, and it is RARELY forgiving. At your lvl, with a good group, you could easily do the Grave Yard and even venture into the castle. But when I talk about Mistmoore rarely being forgiving, I'm not talking about having to run to zone, I'm talking about DEATH!<br><br>Want a true challenge? Want to have to think? Want to feel that fear rise in your stomach when you move into the Castle? MM should do it for ya. I recommend reading up before you just show up though. It is a tricky and dangerous zone.<br><br>And, if you don't like MM, you can try the Estate of Unrest. At 31 you should do well there in the Basement or Towers for several more levels or just soloing on the second floor.  And it's all undead, so Paladins can really shine with their Invis to Undead and Expulse Undead spells, not to mention if you have a Ghoulbane.  Unrest is fun and I still go there from time to time, but MM is the place!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
