	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ahhhhhh, lvl 31, lvl after old hell hehe. I hunted at FM's giant fort, until i realized that was bad exp, then i went to Unrest. Besides Unrest being my and my guild's favorite hunting/meeting place, you are now in the levels where it REALLY shines for you. Get in a ghost or alter group, invis vs undead yourself and run through the basement to the ghost room. There spawns Hags, TT's, DT's, Schroom's, Werebats, GDB's, Barbed's, and old Garanel Rucksif(ghost). after a time down here, you will hopefully have gotten a feel for the place and begin to like it. This may as well be some of the best exp and hunting in group exp for lvls 30-35. FS drops here, along with bronze armor, and good coin. Also rare drops are the jagged bands from the ghost, and the DWB's from the ghost. ( all of this being rare, is assuming the ghost doesnt pop for a little while, happens a lot) Also, once you reach lvl 34 or so, you can solo at the blood pool for incredible exp. I remember soloing here at lvl 35 at the rate of 1 bub per 1 and 1/2 hours of playing. Great fun, and when there's not a ghost group, you can invis yourself and head upstairs to camp the ghoul magi room for some cash. Also, you can meet new and good people by just Powerleveling them from like 9-15 or so. Only take s a little while, and you meet a new person, and maybe ave some fun in between. So try Unrest for good exp and loot. OH and uh, BTW Cazic Thule SUCKS for a dungeon for exp( in my experience)<br>Zomor-bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
