	   <tr><td colspan=2>well well, i have heard enough crap about paladins being bad.&nbsp;&nbsp;the only charachter i have ever had (and i been playing since october) is a paladin and i've had nothing but fun!!  i can't remember all the times people have offered to bare my child after saving there ass's with a loh, or the times that while the warrior is sitting waiting for life to regen i just cast a few heals and i am full.  around level 27-28 i started to understand how to really play the paladin, and soloing suddenly became an option.  Simply having a slugfest with a mob is boring, seeing who can deal the most damage, but with a paladin you have to think, strategize, and budget your mana.  you have to time the LoH just right so that u use it only when its ABSOLUTELY neccesary.  now that i have achieved level 30, the paladin is even more fun.  my wepon procs, i got a symbol which is just cool, healing which heals me muchos, and to top it all off the exp penalty has been removed and LoH now heals an extra 200!!! i'm having the best time on my paladin and if you can't pick a class to make, i'd choose paladin if i were you.  then again monks and necro's are pretty cool, lol.<br><br>    Hakadar Gimlikin, lvl 31 paladin of the Quellious server<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
