	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Gorm, I couldn't agree more!&nbsp;&nbsp;Nice post that well explains the benefits of a Paladin at a higher lvl than myself and gives some good advice to all Paladins.  The root, heal and armor combination of a Paladin is very powerful and the ability to top-off the party members by healing that last 100 pts, so the Cleric can med and regain mana, is a great plus as well.  <br><br>And I can't stress how important it is to keep ALL your combat skills up!  I know because I didn't do it and then struggled like hell to get my 1-hs and bash up when I finally got Ghoulbane. Don't just stick with 2-hs in your teens and 20's. I agree it is a more useful skill at those times, but DON'T DO IT!! You need to switch off from time to time and ensure everything is maxed.  The higher you get the more casters you encounter, the more damage they can do, and the more important it becomes to bash them and interrupt their casting!  All you have to do is go to Mistmoore and fight something from the GraveYard that heals itself over and over again during battle, and you'll see what I mean. You have the mob almost dead, miss a bash, and watch his sliver of health go back to 3/4th full where you have to re-kill him all over again! The party is counting on you to bash, stun and interrupt casting. Don't let them down by having a poor bash ability.<br><br>I would even go as far as including 1-hb and 2-hb in that category of skills to keep up.  There are some awesome uber Bashing items Paladins can use at later levels. The last thing you want to have happen when you're lvl 45 is get a chance at one of these uber items and realize your Bash skill is a TWO!!  I can't tell you how hard it is to get your skill up later in life.  Do it while you're young!  And besides, who says you always have to use Swords and Axes?  I can certainly picture my Dwarf with a BIG honkin hammer, smashing knees all across Velious!<br><br>You hit the nail right on the head when you said:<br><br>Play a pally the right way and you'll love this class. Play it the wrong way and you'll be just another person posting "Why Pally Sux"!<br><br>I think too many players want the Paladin to be a warrior, and we are not 'just' a warrior. To play him as such will only lead to disappointment as the warrior next to you outdamages you, kicks, bashes and gets Critical Hits. If you are one of those players thinking Paladins bite, perhaps you should look at how you're playing him/her?  Play him as he is intended and he is one of the best classes in the game, hands down, IMHO.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
