	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, heres the deal. I am a lvl 40 pally. When i can't find a group, I go solo the EXG camp in sol A. I have so much melatite I can't give the stuff away. If you can find a cleric or druid or shaman partner, I am sure they would want the shield off of the EXG anyway (its like 9 or 10 wis, You may want one yourself) and at 40 the mobs there die easy and still give good exp. after the patch and the experience increase, It is a good place to hunt with a partner. Just remember that the EXG is 100% magic resistant, so really only melee attacks and a damage shield will help against it (gonna need that partner to heal you and help beat her down when she runs) After 1 camp of like 7 hours or so (partner and I did Gabbie too for the molten cloak) We walked away with 3 shields, 1 Charred BP, 1 Cloak, Couple Mith quills (worthless btw) and like 10 or 11 melatite. Should solve your problem. <br><br>Also, If you can't get a partner to help you camp it, Sit at the zone line and auction for it for say 10pp or so. Most people would rather sell it to you than a vendor for like 8 silver or even drag it to Ebay commons (Heavy stuff) and try to auction it there.<br><br>One last thing, posts said that it is most commonly found on model MB and MC clocks, but it seems more random off of them all to me.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hope this Helps!  <br><br>Kassoff Holyknight<br>Lvl 40 Paladin of Emarr<br>Master Smithie<br>Emarr Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
