	   <tr><td colspan=2>Now that you have your lvl 22nd spells, most importantly your Invis to Undead, and assuming you've been practicing your Ward Undead, The Estate of Unrest, located off Dagnors Cauldron, is a great place to practice your true divine purpose as a Paladin which is to slay undead!&nbsp;&nbsp;But be warned, Unrest is a tricky zone with a deadly long tunnel that leads into and out of the dungeon that makes for long runs to zone.  <br><br>Trains are common place and the pathing of the inhabitants is most bizarre and difficult. But, with a little practice, some good grouping, and good spell ability, you can do quite well there, either in a group or solo!<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>30th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
